  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "A new mother confides she doesn't feel the instant bond she expected with her baby. How do you reassure her?",
  "response_text": "I'm really sorry to hear that the new mother is not feeling the instant bond she expected with her baby. It's important to remember that every parent's experience is unique, and it's completely normal for feelings to develop over time. Here are a few things that might help:\n\n1. Acknowledge her feelings: Let her know that it's okay to feel this way and that many new parents experience similar feelings.\n2. Encourage interaction: Suggest spending more time with the baby, skin-to-skin contact, and feeding the baby, as these activities can help foster a bond.\n3. Seek support: Encourage her to reach out to her partner, family, or friends for support. Sharing her feelings with others can help her feel less alone.\n4. Self-care: Remind her to take care of herself, as it's important for her emotional well-being. This could include getting enough rest, eating well, and taking time for herself.\n5. Professional help: If her feelings persist, it might be helpful to speak with a healthcare provider or a mental health professional, as they can provide guidance and support.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 9\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
